name: Rick
line: Learning to fly this thing, Morty, it's gonna be really liberating. Y-Y-You’re gonna be free to go on all kinds of errands for me.

name: Morty
line: Cool.

name: Rick
line: See that planet right there? Don’t fly too close to that planet. Someone’ll come out and try to wash your windshield.  Hold on.  Yup. Yeah, I have it. Where do you wanna meet? Alright, cool.  Alright Morty, lesson’s over. We got some business to attend to a few lightminutes south of here.

name: Jerry
line: Oh, you still use ‘south’ in space?

name: Rick
line: WHOA! Jesus, Jerry, what the hell are you doing here?!

name: Jerry
line: What are you talking about? We agreed a boy’s father should be present when he’s learning to drive.

name: Rick
line: I guess I remember that.  Wow. And you’ve just been back there this whole time? Amazing. Well we don’t have time to take him to Earth, Morty. Head for 3124-917.

name: Jerry
line: Cool! Looks like I’m comin’ along for an adventure!

name: Rick
line: Yep.

name: Morty
line: This is where we’re going?

name: Rick
line: Nope.  This is. You can park in a handicapped spot, Morty. Anything with less than eight limbs is considered disabled here.

name: Jerry-Sitter
line: Well look at this fella.  Aren’t you handsome?

name: Jerry
line: Thank you! I’m Jerry.

name: Jerry-Sitter
line: Oh, I know you are. Did you come here in a spaceship?

name: Jerry
line: I’m travelling with my son and father-in-law. Uh, wait, are they coming?

name: Jerry-Sitter
line: Oh, they’ll be back soon.

name: Jerry
line: What?

name: Pajama Jerry
line: I don’t know how this works!

name: Underpants Jerry
line: Help me!

name: Jerry
line: What the hell?

name: Pajama Jerry
line: I know, right?

name: Tuxedo Jerry
line: Oh, what the hell?

name: Jerry
line: I know, right?

name: Morty
line: Jerryboree? You created a daycare for my dad?

name: Rick
line: You kidding? I wish I had this idea. Well… I did have this idea, but I wish I was the version of me that owned it. That guy’s rich.

name: Receptionist
line: Don’t forget to check the reason for your drop-off.

name: Rick
line: Trust me Morty, I’ve heard stories from other Ricks. Jerrys don’t tend to last five minutes off of Earth. This is a totally unregistered cross-temporal asteroid. Here they can romp and play with other Jerrys. It couldn’t be safer.

name: Rick
line: Hey Morty, hang onto this. That number’s your dad. If you lose it, we’re not gonna be able to get him back.

name: Rick
line: Okay, wait here.

name: Morty
line: I wanna come with.

name: Rick
line: Don’t come with. It’s boring, it’s  business stuff.

name: Morty
line: What kinda business do you do in a garage? You know, this seems a little shady.

name: Rick
line: Right, like nothing shady ever happened in a fully furnished office? You ever hear about Wall Street Morty? Y-You know what those guys do in th—in their fancy board rooms? They take their balls, and they dip ‘em in cocaine, and they wipe ‘em all over each other. You know, Grandpa goes around, and he does his business in public because Grandpa isn’t shady.

name: Rick
line: Ah, crap.  Hey, what’s up?

name: Krombopulos Michael
line: Hey, Rick! Haha! Here you go, three thousand Flurbos! D’you have the weapon?

name: Rick
line: Can… Can we please…? This is my grandson, Morty.

name: Krombopulos Michael
line: Well hi Morty! I’m Krombopulos Michael! I’m an assassin. I buy guns from your grandpa.

name: Rick
line: Ugh.  Here, now go away.

name: Krombopulos Michael
line: Ooh, yeah, this looks deadly. So this shoots antimatter? My target can’t be killed with regular matter. Nice to meet you, Morty! Listen, if you ever need anybody murdered,  please give me a call. I’m very discrete—

name: Rick
line: Y-Y-Y-You’re gonna give him your card?!

name: Krombopulos Michael
line: I have no code of ethics, I will kill anyone, anywhere! Children, animals, old people, doesn’t matter. I just love killin’!

name: Morty
line: …You sell weapons to killers for money?

name: Rick
line: Ugh… You’ve got what the intergalactic call a very planetary mindset, Morty. It’s more complicated out here! These are Flurbos. Do you understand what two humans can accomplish with three thousand of these?

name: Morty
line: Uh, what?

name: Rick
line: An entire afternoon at Blips and Chiiiitz!

name: Rick
line: Aw, this place is the best. It’s got beer, games, prizes, and you can never tell what time it is.

name: Morty
line: You sold a gun to a murderer so you could play video games?

name: Rick
line: Yeah, sure, if you spend all day shuffling words around you can make anything sound bad, Morty.  Here, check this out.

name: Roy
line: Ah!

name: Roy’s mother
line: Roy, what’s wrong?

name: Roy
line: I…had a nightmare. I was with an old man… He put a helmet on me.

name: Roy’s mother
line: It’s just a fever. Get some sleep, I don’t want you missing school on Monday.

name: Teacher
line: I want you kids to look around you today and think about your future.  Now is the time in your life when anything is possible.

name: Announcer
line: Spiraling perfectly, it’s gonna be caught by Roy Parsons! Roy Parsons is at the 20!  Now he’s at the 10! Nothing can stop Roy the Rocket! Touchdown!

name: Roy’s wife
line: I just think it’s time to get realistic. Have you talked to my father about the carpet store? Roy?

name: Doctor
line: Had we caught it sooner… Well, hindsight is 20-20, Roy. What’s important is that we move quickly.

name: Roy
line: I’m not…ready to die…

name: Roy’s wife
line: You’re not going to.

name: Customer
line: Hey, thanks for the carpet, Roy.

name: Voice
line: Hey Roy, you pull those Persian off-white shags for the clearance sale?

name: Roy
line: Whoa. Sh-shit! Shit!

name: Morty
line: Whoa! What the hell?! Wha—Where am I?! What the hell?!

name: Rick
line: Fifty-five years. Not bad, Morty. You kinda wasted your thirties though with that whole birdwatching phase.

name: Morty
line: W… Where’s my wife?

name: Rick
line: Morty. You were just playing a game. It’s called Roy. Snap out of it, come on.

name: Morty
line: I’m Morty… You’re Rick… Hey, you sold a gun to a guy that kills people!

name: Rick
line: Lookit this. You beat cancer and then you went back to work at the carpet store? Boo.

name: Morty
line: Don’t dodge the issue, Rick! Selling a gun to a hitman is the same as pulling the trigger!

name: Rick
line: It’s also the same as doing nothing. If Krombopulos Michael wants someone dead, there’s not a lot anybody can do to stop him. That’s why he does it for a living? Now if you’ll excuse me, it’s time to thrash your Roy score.

name: Morty
line: You could stop this killing from happening, Rick! You know, y-you did a bad thing selling that gun, but you could undo it if you wanted!

name: Rick
line: Uh-huh, yeah, that’s the difference between you and me, Morty. I never go back to the carpet store.

name: Alien
line: Holy shit! This guy’s taking Roy off the grid!  This guy doesn’t have a social security number for Roy!

name: Jerry
line: Hi, I’m sorry, I think there was a misunderstanding. I’m an adult and would like to go home, please.

name: Jerry-Sitter
line: Well of course! Right through that tube.

name: Jerry
line: Unbelievable.

name: Jerry-Sitter
line: You’re doing great!

name: Jerry
line: I know how to crawl in a tube.  Ugh… Come on… This is harder than it looks…  Whoooooaaaa!

name: Pink-shirt Jerry
line: Marco?  Marco?

name: Other Jerry
line: Come find me.

name: Pink-shirt Jerry
line: Marco?

name: Jerry
line: You guys are enjoying this? Don’t you feel a little… patronized?

name: Pink-shirt Jerry
line: How so?

name: Daycare Beth
line: Jerry!

name: Other Jerry
line: Beeeth.

name: Jerry
line: Oh, come on, this is ridiculous!

name: Daycare Beth
line: I love you, Jerry!

name: Jerry
line: Aw… Beth…

name: Daycare Beth
line: Who wants to come watch Midnight Run with director’s commentary on?

name: Jerrys
line: Oh! Yes! Definitely!

name: Daycare Beth
line: First one there gets to adjust the picture settings!

name: Jerry
line: The factory tint setting is always too high!

name: Other Jerry
line: Out of my way!

name: Another Jerry
line: The factory tint setting is always too high!

name: Krombopulos Michael
line: Oh boy, here I go killin’ again!

name: Ship
line: You have arrived at Krombopulos Michael. Your destination is below.

name: Morty
line: All out of off-white Persians…  Oh man, wha-wh-wh-what have I done?!

name: Gromflomite
line: Drop the gun!

name: Morty
line: You don’t understand! This guy was gonna kill someone!

name: Gromflomite
line: I guess that makes two of us.

name: Rick
line: What are you doing Morty?! This is a Galactic Federation outpost! Look, I don’t have time to tell you my entire backstory, but Grandpa and government don’t get along!

name: Fart
line: You saved my life!

name: Rick
line: What?

name: Morty
line: Huh?! Are you Krombopulos Michael’s target? W-Wwwwhat’s your name?

name: Fart
line: My kind has no use for names. I communicate through what you call “Jessica’s feet.” No, “telepathy.”

name: Rick
line: Oh, good job, Morty. Y-Y-Y-You killed my best customer but you saved a mind-reading fart!

name: Fart
line: I like this name, ‘Fart.’ Morty, would you kindly release me by pulling that lever to the left of my cell? I am in great pain.

name: Rick
line: Morty, don’t do it.  Morty…  Morty, you idiot!

name: Morty
line: Oh crap, let’s get you outta here!

name: Rick
line: We can’t get him outta here. He’s gaseous. He’s not gonna make it through a portal, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Well then I guess we’re all getting in the car! Right, uh…

name: Fart
line: Fart.

name: Morty
line: No! Jus-j-j-just get in the car!

name: Rick
line: Morty, come on, I-I wanna go back to Blips and Chitz. I don’t wanna deal with this!

name: Morty
line: Y-You’ve been clear on the fact that you don’t wanna help, so just go away!

name: Fart
line: More are coming.

name: Rick
line: Screw this. I’m out.

name: Morty
line: Oooh…! Come on, come on!

name: Gromflomite
line: Get out of the vehicle made of garbage or we will open fire!

name: Morty
line: Oh no no no!

name: Gromflomite
line: Open fire!

name: Rick
line: Stupid-ass fart-saving carpet-store motherfucker!  Move!

name: Rick
line: Wait, did you fuck with my seat settings?

name: Fart
line: More are coming.

name: Morty
line: Rick!

name: Rick
line: Yeah, yeah.

name: Gearhead
line: Your geldon convertor is pretty dinged up.

name: Rick
line: That’s ‘cause my grandson drives like a male Obavradian. Yeah, I said it. Some stereotypes are based in fact.

name: Gearhead
line: Actually, it’s because of years of neglect. You really need to respect your gears, Rick. To you, they’re just wheels with teeth, but in my culture, wars have been fought, entire—

name: Rick
line: So I’ve heard. Just fix it.  I don’t think the Gromflomites can track us now, but it looks like we’re gonna be here for awhile.  Or, ya know, if you still have that gun K. Michael dropped, we can finish the job and go home.

name: Fart
line: You do understand I’m telepathic, right?

name: Rick
line: I’m being polite.

name: Morty
line: Rick, we’re taking him back where he belongs!

name: Rick
line: Yeah, where’s that? Are you going on a quest to find he who smelt it?

name: Fart
line: I came here accidentally through a wormhole located in what you call “get out of my head, Fart, I know you’re in here, la la la la—” No, in what you call the Promethean Nebula.

name: Rick
line: Oh great, just a hop, skip, and an 800 lightyear jump!

name: Morty
line: You know, you can leave any time you want, Rick.

name: Rick
line: Whatever you wanna do you little punk-ass little bitch…

name: Fart
line: Thank you, Morty. You are not like other carbon-based life forms. You put the value of all life above your own.

name: Morty
line: That’s how things should be. It’s how they could be.

name: Fart
line: I could not agree more.

name: Fart
line: The world can be one together / Cosmos without hatred / Stars like diamonds in your eyes. / The ground can be space  / With feet marching toward a peaceful sky. / All the moonmen want things their way / But we make sure they see the sun. / Goodbye, moonmen / You say goodbye, moonmen. / Goodby—

name: Rick
line: Shut the fuck up about moonmen! This isn’t a musical number. This is a fucking operation, we gotta be cool and fucking lay low!

name: Random Jerry
line: Duck, duck, birdie?  Very funny!

name: Jerry
line: Here comes another funny…

name: Other Jerry
line: Hahaha! Oh, this place is great.

name: Jerry
line: I almost wish I could stay longer than one day.

name: Other Jerry
line: You just might.

name: Jerry
line: W-What do you mean?

name: Other Jerry
line: These are the Jerrys whose Ricks and Mortys never came back.  …They live here now.

name: Jerry
line: Uuuum…

name: Gear Anchor
line: No gear turnings as of yet in the curious case of these unidentified humanoid fugitives  reportedly at large somewhere within the Gear System.

name: Rick
line: Son of a…  Why were the Gromflomites holding you prisoner? What the fuck is so valuable about you?

name: Fart
line: I am no more valuable than life itself. However, I am able to alter the composition of atoms, like this.  That was oxygen. I added seventy-one protons to it.

name: Rick
line: Ah, terrific. The fart that pooped gold. No wonder every cop in the system is lookin’ for us!  Any species that gets a hold of this thing is gonna use it to take over the galaxy. Do you know how inconvenient that’s gonna be to my work?

name: Rick
line: Somebody dropped the dime on us. Gearhead…

name: Gearhead
line: I’m sorry, Rick. The reward on your head is too high. And like you always say, you gotta look out for Number One.

name: Rick
line: Number One is me, asshole! You’re supposed to be my friend!

name: Gearhead
line: Friend? Do you even know my real name? It’s Revolio Clockberg Junior. I belong to an entire species of gear people. Calling me ‘Gearhead’ is like calling a Chinese person ‘Asia-face.’

name: Gearhead
line: No, not twigs!

name: Rick
line: Two things I wanna make clear to everybody in this room. Never betray me, and it’s time to go.

name: Gear Policeman #1
line: Nobody move!

name: Gear Policeman #2
line: Oh my god.

name: Gear Policeman #1
line: Are those…?

name: Rick
line: Hey Morty, remember when you said selling a gun was as bad as pulling the trigger? How do you feel about all these people getting killed because of your choices?

name: Morty
line: I did the right thing, Rick!

name: Rick
line: Tell that to Gearhead’s gearsticles.

name: Morty
line: You did that!

name: Rick
line: Wrong! I’d be playin’ Roy right now. At a certain point, my hands are tied, Morty.

name: Jerry
line: I can’t believe Rick did this. This is the eighth to the last straw.

name: Bearded Jerry
line: Ante up.

name: Jerry
line: You know what?  Screw it! I have a better gamble for your guys.  I say we escape.

name: Bearded Jerry
line: If you want to leave, you can just go out the front door.

name: Tank-top Jerry
line: You think we’re kept here against our will? That would be illegal.

name: Jerry
line: But… If you can leave, then why are you still here?

name: Buzzcut Jerry
line: Same reason as you.  …We’re Jerrys.

name: Jerry
line: I’m leaving.

name: Jerry-Sitter
line: Okay then, that was always allowed.

name: Rick
line: Morty, take the wheel!

name: Morty
line: Whoa, whoa!

name: Rick
line: Whoa!

name: Rick
line: Geez, dammit, Morty! Who taught you to fly this thing?!  Haha, I’m kidding, I know that’s on me.

name: Morty
line: Um, Rick!

name: Rick
line: Shit. Well, I guess this is it.

name: Fart
line: Morty, crack the window.

name: Fart
line: I wonder why Greg is always so critical of my girlfriend.

name: Officer
line: Well… He’d probably like to have me to himself, that’s how friends are.

name: Fart
line: Or does he want her to himself?

name: Fart
line: The world can be one together / Cosmos without hatred / Stars like diamonds in your eyes.

name: Officer
line: My life is a fucking joke.

name: Fart
line: Goodbye, moonmen. / You say, goodbye, moonmen.

name: Fart
line: Goodbye, moonmen…  Alright, let’s proceed.

name: Rick
line: Damn. Can’t blame that on the dog. …Talk about silent but deadly. I-I’ve seen some nerve gas but ga- th-this gas got some nerve! Haha, you know what I’m sayin’?

name: Morty
line: Are you done?

name: Rick
line: I’ll let you know, Morty. Gone with the wind, am I right? If you don’t like that one, Morty, an alt on that one could be, like…if I said Gasablanca! …Alright, I’m done.  Let’s get to the Promethean Nebula, so my grandson can finish savin’ a life!

name: Garblovian
line: Ga-ga blahg blahg?

name: Jerry
line: Um… Earth, please?

name: Jerry
line: Um… Is this… Do I pay?

name: Garblovian
line: Agah blahg-blah!

name: Jerry
line: Sorry!

name: Jerry
line: Hmm. Hmm…  Agh!

name: Garblovian
line: Agah blahg blahg?

name: Jerry
line: I don’t…

name: Garblovian
line: Agah blahg!

name: Jerry
line: What do you want?

name: Garblovian
line: Agah blahg blah—

name: Jerry
line: Oh!  Ahahaaaahhhhh….

name: Jerry
line: Uhhh… Huhhh….  Oooh!

name: Tank-top Jerry
line: Hey, are you the one that left?

name: Tank-top Jerry
line: I get it. It’s… uh… a hassle out there.

name: Jerry
line: Right? Who needs that?

name: Other Jerrys
line: Right? Not me.

name: Paul
line: Oh-ho, not us!

name: Jerry
line: Uh… Who are you?

name: Paul
line: Oh, excuse me. Paul Fleishman.  Infinite timelines! In some of them Beth remarries.

name: Jerry
line: …Geez…

name: Paul
line: Don’t worry. I treat Beth very well, and I do not overstep my bounds with Morty. Every kid needs a dad, but there’s no replacing you. Hey, you wanna give us a hand with this?  We’re trying to figure out how to get the sound coming through the stereo instead of the TV. I-I-I don’t—It’s very difficult.

name: Jerry
line: Oh. Uh, well, is there an Aux input?

name: Tank-top Jerry
line: I tried that, but there’s two different colors.

name: Various Jerrys
line: Uh… There’s two different colors.

name: Fart
line: The wormhole is seventy of what you call ‘meters’ what you call ‘north’ of what you call ‘here.’

name: Rick
line: Fine. Morty, take your fart to his hole and say your goodbyes. I’m gonna find some fuel and take a biiiig fat Morty.  That’s my new word for ‘shit’ because of today’s events.

name: Fart
line: Here it is. This should take me back to my kind.

name: Morty
line: I’m gonna miss you, um, Fart. I’m really sorry your name became Fart.

name: Fart
line: I will be back soon, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Really?

name: Fart
line: After I return to the others with this location, we will be back for your cleansing.

name: Morty
line: Um… Cleansing…?

name: Fart
line: Carbon-based life is a threat to all higher life. To us, you are what you would call a disease. Wherever we discover you, we cure it. You said yourself that life must be protected even through sacrifice.  You haven’t changed your mind about that. I can sense your thoughts. Morty.

name: Morty
line: Um… Before you go… Could you sing a… C-Could you sing for me again?

name: Fart
line: Yes, Morty.  Cosmos without hatred / Blinding stars of cosmic light / Quasars shine through endless night / And everything is one in the beauty / And now we say goodby—

name: Fart
line: Morty… Why… Why?

name: Morty
line: Goodbye.

name: Rick
line: So did you guys make out a little bit? Is he gonna send you a postcard?  Man, that guy hit the lottery when he crossed paths with you.

name: Rick
line: Morty, I know I picked on your core beliefs and decision making a lot today, but I am glad you insisted on gettin’ that fart home. You know, at least all the death and destruction wasn’t for nothin’, you know?  You miss your fart friend, huh? Well I’ve got a little surprise for you, buddy. While you were gone I found another wormhole with millions of beings just like him on the other side and they’re all coming to visit.

name: Morty
line: What?! Rick! No, you can’t!

name: Rick
line: Too late, Morty. The hole’s opening.

name: Morty
line: No, no, Rick! You don’t understand!

name: Rick
line: Th-there’s a lot more where that came from too.

name: Rick
line: Hey.  Hey bro. How many people was your Morty responsible for killing today?

name: Other Rick
line: None, we chilled at Blips and Chitz all day, ain’t that right homie?

name: Other Morty
line: Darn right bro! Roy rules!

name: Other Rick
line: Haha!

name: Rick
line: Must be nice… Hey, Morty, there’s our Jerry.

name: Jerry
line: Mm, I missed you. Hey, Rick.

name: Rick
line: Glad you’re safe Jerry. What do you say we go home?

name: Jerry
line: I’d like that.

name: Another Rick
line: Hey, wait, do you have 5126?

name: Rick
line: Uh, I’m not sure. Morty.

name: Other Rick
line: Uh, that’s a Blips and Chitz ticket.

name: Morty
line: What?!

name: Rick
line: Way to go, Morty. Eh, whatever.

name: Jerrys
line: Uh… W-wait, what?

name: Ricks
line: Alright, come on, Jerry.

name: Announcer
line: Are you tired of the same daily droll? Well, get on over to Blips and Chitz!  We got, uh… one game! We got a whole bunch of games here! Uh, we got chabos and flobos and you can shoot things! Get on over here and play the games! Use your Flurbos to get tickets! Roy 2 just got here! G-Get over here at Ch… Chips and Chitz!

name: Rick
line: It’s the coolest place in the world! Hahahaha, I g- I get to be in a commercial!
